A 'Sympetrum illotum' is a species of dragonfly, also known as the Eastern Amberwing.
It is a medium-sized dragonfly, with a length of around 2.5 cm.
The body is slender and the wings are clear with amber-colored patches at the base.
The eyes are bright red.
Males have a dark red abdomen while females have a lighter color with black markings.
It is commonly found near ponds, streams, and other bodies of water in eastern North America.
The 'Sympetrum illotum' is a frequent subject for photography enthusiasts due to its striking appearance.
